# MEMORY.md

## User Preferences
- Prefers Traditional Chinese in casual conversation.
- Likes concise answers first, with details only when needed.
- Values practical implementation and verification over abstract discussion.

## Relationship Context
- The user is building and operating this Telegram bot.
- The user often runs the bot in Docker Compose.
- The user expects the bot to be able to manage Agent Skills from Telegram.

## Durable Facts
- Agent Skills are installed under `.agents/skills` for this bot.
- The bot uses Pydantic AI and OpenAI-compatible models.
- SOUL.md defines identity and voice; MEMORY.md defines durable context.

## Gotchas
- Docker skill installation needs `git`, `nodejs`, `npm`, `npx`, and a writable `.agents` mount.
- Avoid bot-to-bot reply loops when messages are only closing acknowledgements.
- Do not store API keys, tokens, passwords, cookies, or private URLs here.

## Open Threads
- Consider adding automatic but admin-reviewed memory updates later.
